history.content:
At this point, the undeclared seats for 5-6 terms in attendance have filled, unfortunately.

For the past several semesters, it has worked out in the end for almost everyone to get off the EE16A waitlist by the 5th week of the semester. The handful of people who remained on the WL did not change their lab and/or discussion despite several reminders from me. I can't guarantee it of course, but it seems likely that this will happen again. I'm guessing the Fri 5-8PM lab will not fill.

children.subject: If I'm 143 on the waitlist and am a freshman LSCS, will I be able to get into the course? (I also do not know how to tell from the "funky rules.")...

history.content:
If I'm 99 of 500 on the waitlist for 16A, is there a good chance I'll get into the course? I can never tell. I know there are some funky rules for how many seats they reserve for undeclared non-freshmen. I'm undeclared CS going into my junior fall semester (declaring this summer (hopefully) (RIP)).

I was enrolled in 61C, but some people told me I should wait until spring because the profs are better & take EE16A instead because Alon is supposed to be good. 

Would it be better to just re-enroll in 61C instead?
